│ incoming GEPs (via NW &= ...), but it does not intersect the inbounds flag. It likely sets inbounds on the new  │
│ merged GEP based solely on the first operand, which can introduce poison when some incoming GEPs are not        │
│ inbounds. The fix is to track an AllInBounds flag initialized from the first GEP and AND it with each incoming  │
│ GEP’s isInBounds() result; then only set NewGEP inbounds if AllInBounds is true. I will patch                   │
│ InstCombinePHI.cpp accordingly and submit the patch.                                                            │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ applypatch << 'PATCH'                                                                                           │
│ *** Begin Patch                                                                                                 │
│ *** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombinePHI.cpp                                             │
│ @@                                                                                                              │
│    // Remember flags of the first phi-operand getelementptr.                                                    │
│ -  GEPNoWrapFlags NW = FirstInst->getNoWrapFlags();                                                             │
│ +  GEPNoWrapFlags NW = FirstInst->getNoWrapFlags();                                                             │
│ +  // Intersect 'inbounds' across all incoming GEPs. It is only correct to keep                                 │
│ +  // 'inbounds' on the merged GEP if every incoming GEP is inbounds; otherwise,                                │
│ +  // we may introduce poison on paths that were previously non-poison.                                         │
│ +  bool AllInBounds = FirstInst->isInBounds();                                                                  │
│ @@                                                                                                              │
│ -    NW &= GEP->getNoWrapFlags();                                                                               │
│ +    NW &= GEP->getNoWrapFlags();                                                                               │
